# Plan: Workflow Refinements & Location Assignment

## Goal
1. **Default Quantity**: When a user successfully scans a barcode, the default "정상수량" (Normal Quantity) should be automatically set to `1` instead of `0` to speed up the workflow.
2. **Barcode Display Accuracy**: Clarify the UI to show exactly what barcode was scanned vs the internal product code, to reduce confusion.
3. **Location (Cell) Assignment for High-Volume Returns**: Master administrators need a way to aggregate the total expected return quantities across all stores per product, and assign a "Fixed Cell" (고정 보관함/로케이션) for high-volume items to optimize warehouse placement.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer ([models.py](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py))
- **[MODIFY]** [models.py](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py)
  - Add a `fixed_cell` (String, nullable) column to [ProductMaster](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py#5-12) to store the assigned warehouse location.

### Backend ([main.py](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/main.py))
- **[NEW]** `GET /api/aggregate-plans`
  - Sums the `expected_qty` from all [ReturnPlan](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py#13-20) entries, grouped by `product_code`.
  - Joins with [ProductMaster](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py#5-12) to attach `name` and `fixed_cell`.
  - Returns a list sorted by `total_expected_qty` in descending order.
- **[NEW]** `PUT /api/products/{code}/cell`
  - Simple endpoint to update the `fixed_cell` value of a specific product.

